 {"id":"brenner_bot-a0r7","title":"Task: Implement Transition Validator","description":"# Task: Implement Transition Validator

## Objective
Implement the core transition function that validates and executes state changes on hypotheses.

## Implementation Details

### File Location
`apps/web/src/lib/hypothesis-transitions.ts` (extend)

### Core Function
```typescript
export interface TransitionResult {
  success: boolean;
  hypothesis?: Hypothesis;
  transition?: StateTransition;
  error?: TransitionError;
}

export interface TransitionError {
  code: 'INVALID_TRANSITION' | 'HYPOTHESIS_NOT_FOUND' | 'MISSING_REQUIREMENTS';
  message: string;
  details?: Record<string, unknown>;
}

export async function transitionHypothesis(
  hypothesisId: string,
  trigger: TransitionTrigger,
  options?: {
    triggeredBy?: string;
    reason?: string;
    metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;
  }
): Promise<TransitionResult> {
  // 1. Load hypothesis
  const hypothesis = await getHypothesisById(hypothesisId);
  if (!hypothesis) {
    return {
      success: false,
      error: {
        code: 'HYPOTHESIS_NOT_FOUND',
        message: `Hypothesis ${hypothesisId} not found`,
      },
    };
  }

  // 2. Determine target state from trigger
  const triggerConfig = TRIGGER_TRANSITIONS[trigger];
  if (!triggerConfig.from.includes(hypothesis.state)) {
    return {
      success: false,
      error: {
        code: 'INVALID_TRANSITION',
        message: `Cannot ${trigger} hypothesis in state ${hypothesis.state}`,
        details: { validFromStates: triggerConfig.from },
      },
    };
  }

  // 3. Check transition-specific requirements
  if (trigger === 'kill' && !options?.triggeredBy) {
    return {
      success: false,
      error: {
        code: 'MISSING_REQUIREMENTS',
        message: 'Kill transition requires triggeredBy (test ID or reason)',
      },
    };
  }

  // 4. Create transition record
  const transition: StateTransition = {
    hypothesisId,
    fromState: hypothesis.state,
    toState: triggerConfig.to,
    trigger,
    triggeredBy: options?.triggeredBy,
    reason: options?.reason,
    metadata: options?.metadata,
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
  };

  // 5. Update hypothesis state
  const updatedHypothesis = {
    ...hypothesis,
    state: triggerConfig.to,
    updatedAt: transition.timestamp,
  };

  // 6. Persist changes
  await updateHypothesis(hypothesisId, {
    state: updatedHypothesis.state,
    updatedAt: updatedHypothesis.updatedAt,
  });
  await logTransition(transition);

  return {
    success: true,
    hypothesis: updatedHypothesis,
    transition,
  };
}
```

### Transition-Specific Requirements
| Trigger | Required Fields |
|---------|-----------------|
| kill | triggeredBy (test ID), reason |
| refine | metadata.childId (new hypothesis ID) |
| validate | triggeredBy (test ID) |
| park | reason (optional but recommended) |
| activate | (none) |
| reactivate | (none) |

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Transition function validates state machine rules
- [ ] Invalid transitions return structured errors
- [ ] Terminal states cannot be transitioned
- [ ] Transition-specific requirements enforced
- [ ] Hypothesis state updated atomically
- [ ] Transition logged for history

## Dependencies
- Task: Define State Transition Types

